-- Ted Ligety of U.S. Wins Opening World Cup Giant Ski Slalom
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-10-27T14:59:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-27/ted-ligety-of-u-s-wins-opening-world-cup-giant-ski-slalom.html
U.S. skier Ted Ligety won the
season-opening men’s World Cup giant slalom for a third straight
year today.  Ligety won in an aggregate time of 1 minute 59.50 seconds
at Soelden,  Austria . France’s Alexis Pinturault came second and
overall champion Marcel Hirscher of Austria was third.  Ligety last season won his fourth World Cup skiing giant
slalom season title.  Bode Miller of the U.S. came 19th today, having missed last
season through injury.  Switzerland’s Lara Gut won the women’s giant slalom at
Soelden yesterday.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 